most_relevant.description:
I've been attending this calisthenics class regularly, and it takes a structured and disciplined approach to training. The sessions aim to work the full body almost every day, ensuring that no muscle group is neglected.

There’s a good mix of training formats, including some Tabata-style conditioning and weight lifting for variety and intensity. The class is split into beginner and intermediate levels.

The weekly schedule is intense and steady, which definitely helps build endurance and mental toughness. Saturdays focus on skill work, offering a refreshing shift toward more technical and control-based movements that highlight the essence of calisthenics.

It has well-maintained bars, parallel bars, and workout stations for all skill levels. The atmosphere is great, with a supportive community and plenty of space to train. Whether you’re a beginner like me or an advanced, it’s an excellent spot to improve your strength. Highly recommended!✨

I have been member of Cali Hq for a year, and it's been an amazing experience. The place is well-maintained and has a wide range of equipment suitable for all fitness levels. most_relevant.description:
I rarely write reviews, but my experience at Life Fitness was so disappointing that I feel people should know the truth before wasting their money here.

From day one, I noticed the staff and trainers are completely unqualified. They don’t have the right knowledge about workouts, fitness, or even basic guidance. Instead of motivating or correcting form, they stand around casually, more interested in chatting than helping members. If you’re expecting proper training or support, you will be left frustrated.

The situation is made even worse by the owner’s arrogant attitude. Rather than being approachable and professional, the owner behaves as if customers should be grateful just to enter the gym. Any concerns or feedback are brushed off with rudeness. This kind of attitude makes the entire environment negative and unwelcoming.

A good gym should have:
✅ Qualified trainers who guide you properly
✅ Friendly staff who care about members’ progress
✅ A professional owner who respects customers

Unfortunately, Life Fitness fails in every single one of these areas. For the high prices they charge, members deserve respect, proper fitness advice, and a supportive atmosphere – none of which you’ll find here.

👉 Save your money and your time. There are far better gyms out there where your health goals will be taken seriously and you’ll actually feel valued as a member.

Joining Life Fitness 24x7 has been one of the best decisions I've made for my health and well-being. The gym is open 12pm, which is perfect for my busy schedule. The equipment is modern, well-maintained, and suitable for all fitness levels—from beginners to serious bodybuilders.

What really sets this gym apart is the friendly and knowledgeable staff. The trainers are always ready to help with form corrections, personalized plans, or just a word of motivation. The environment is clean, hygienic, and positive—making workouts something I genuinely look forward to.
